  inventory_warehouse:
    description: 'Specialized configuration guide for inventory management and warehouse
      operations [Refactored: 8 TOP features + defaults] [Refactored: 8 TOP features
      + defaults] [Refactored: 8 TOP features + defaults] [Refactored: 8 TOP features
      + defaults]'
    variables_required:
    - feature_name
    - odoo_version
    template: '{feature_name} configuration determines stock accuracy, warehouse operational
      efficiency, and inventory valuation precision in Odoo {odoo_version}. Unlike
      generic feature configurations that affect isolated workflows, {feature_name}
      changes propagate through purchasing, sales, manufacturing, and accounting modules—a
      misconfigured inventory setting cascades into incorrect cost of goods sold calculations,
      stock discrepancies that force physical inventory counts, and fulfillment delays
      that damage customer relationships.


      {feature_specific_intro}


      ## {feature_name} Configuration Workflow


      {feature_setup_workflow}


      ### Prerequisites and Module Dependencies


      {feature_name} requires specific Odoo modules and base configurations before
      accessing full functionality:


      {prerequisite_configuration}


      Navigate to Apps > search for prerequisite modules > Install. Odoo resolves
      dependencies automatically, but verify each prerequisite shows "Installed" status.
      Missing dependencies cause configuration screens to display incomplete field
      options or throw cryptic validation errors that don''t explicitly state which
      module is missing.


      ## Core Configuration Settings


      {core_settings_section}


      Odoo''s location hierarchy determines how inventory moves between physical and
      virtual locations. Location types (View, Internal, Customer, Vendor, Inventory,
      Production, Transit) control stock valuation and accounting integration. Internal
      locations contribute to on-hand inventory quantities and trigger stock valuation
      entries. Virtual locations (Customer, Vendor) represent external parties and
      affect accounts receivable/payable rather than inventory asset accounts.


      ## Automation and Workflow Configuration


      {automation_configuration}


      ### Inventory Valuation and Costing Methods


      {valuation_configuration}


      Changing valuation methods after significant transaction history requires complex
      data migration and manual accounting adjustments. Consult with your accounting
      team before finalizing valuation configuration—GAAP and IFRS impose restrictions
      on when companies can change valuation methods.


      ## Advanced Configuration Options


      {advanced_options}


      ### Integration with Other Modules


      {feature_name} integrates with purchasing, sales, manufacturing, and accounting
      modules. Configuration changes propagate across integrations:


      {module_integration}


      Test integrations end-to-end: create purchase order > receive inventory > create
      sales order > deliver to customer > verify accounting entries. Integration failures
      manifest as missing stock moves, incorrect valuations, or accounting entry gaps.


      ## User Access and Permission Configuration


      {feature_name} permissions control which users can perform stock adjustments,
      view inventory valuations, or modify warehouse configurations:


      {permission_matrix}


      Segregate duties between warehouse operators (who perform physical movements)
      and inventory controllers (who adjust valuations and run physical counts). Combined
      permissions create fraud risk and compliance violations.


      ## Performance Optimization and Best Practices


      {performance_optimization}


      ### Reporting and Analytics Configuration


      Configure {feature_name} reporting to provide visibility into stock levels,
      movement history, and valuation accuracy:


      {reporting_configuration}


      Custom reports should match existing warehouse management reporting templates.
      If your operations team expects inventory turnover calculated excluding safety
      stock, configure reports identically rather than forcing operational changes
      to match Odoo''s default calculation logic.


      ## Common Configuration Mistakes and Solutions


      {common_mistakes}


      ### Testing and Validation Checklist


      Before declaring {feature_name} configuration complete, validate these scenarios
      with production data volumes:


      {validation_checklist}


      Configuration that performs adequately with 1,000 stock moves often fails at
      100,000+ moves due to database query timeouts, report generation failures, or
      UI slowdowns when selecting locations/products from dropdown lists containing
      thousands of records.

      '
