  accounting_financial:
    description: 'Specialized configuration guide for accounting, financial reporting,
      and compliance [Refactored: 9 TOP features + defaults] [Refactored: 9 TOP features
      + defaults] [Refactored: 9 TOP features + defaults] [Refactored: 9 TOP features
      + defaults]'
    variables_required:
    - feature_name
    - odoo_version
    template: '{feature_name} configuration determines financial statement accuracy,
      regulatory compliance, and management reporting capabilities in Odoo {odoo_version}.
      Unlike operational configurations that affect workflow efficiency, {feature_name}
      changes directly impact auditable financial records, tax compliance obligations,
      and external reporting accuracy—misconfigured accounting settings create audit
      findings, regulatory violations, and financial restatements that damage stakeholder
      trust and trigger compliance penalties.


      {feature_specific_intro}


      ## {feature_name} Configuration Workflow


      {feature_setup_workflow}


      ### Prerequisites and Module Dependencies


      {feature_name} requires specific Odoo modules and base configurations before
      accessing full functionality:


      {prerequisite_configuration}


      Navigate to Apps > search for prerequisite modules > Install. Odoo resolves
      dependencies automatically, but verify each prerequisite shows "Installed" status.
      Missing accounting dependencies cause configuration screens to display incomplete
      field options, throw validation errors during transaction posting, or create
      journal entries with incorrect account mappings.


      ## Core Configuration Settings


      {core_settings_section}


      Accounting configurations establish company-level defaults that constrain all
      financial transactions. Changes to core settings after go-live require data
      migration to reconcile historical transactions with new configuration rules—plan
      configuration carefully during implementation to minimize post-launch changes.


      ## Automation and Workflow Configuration


      {automation_configuration}


      ### Financial Controls and Validation Rules


      {valuation_configuration}


      Financial control configurations prevent posting errors before they enter the
      general ledger. Preventive controls (validation rules, required fields, account
      reconciliation requirements) cost less than detective controls (periodic reconciliations,
      variance analysis) because they stop errors at transaction entry rather than
      discovering them during month-end close.


      ## Advanced Configuration Options


      {advanced_options}


      ### Integration with Other Modules


      {feature_name} integrates with Sales (revenue recognition), Inventory (cost
      of goods sold), Purchasing (accounts payable), and HR (payroll accruals). Configuration
      changes propagate across integrations:


      {module_integration}


      Test integrations systematically: create sales order > ship inventory > generate
      invoice > receive payment > verify accounting entries match expected debits/credits.
      Integration failures manifest as missing journal entries, incorrect account
      coding, or timing differences between module transactions and accounting records.


      ## User Access and Permission Configuration


      {feature_name} permissions control which users can post journal entries, modify
      account reconciliations, or access sensitive financial data:


      {permission_matrix}


      Implement segregation of duties: users who create transactions should not approve
      them, users who approve invoices should not process payments, users who reconcile
      accounts should not post manual journal entries. Combined permissions create
      fraud risk and audit control deficiencies.


      ## Performance Optimization and Best Practices


      {performance_optimization}


      ### Reporting and Analytics Configuration


      Configure {feature_name} reporting to provide visibility into financial position,
      performance trends, and compliance metrics:


      {reporting_configuration}


      Financial reports should match existing financial statement formats to minimize
      disruption for stakeholders consuming reports. If your CFO expects EBITDA calculated
      excluding stock compensation expense, configure reports identically rather than
      forcing finance team to create manual reconciliations between Odoo reports and
      board presentations.


      ## Common Configuration Mistakes and Solutions


      {common_mistakes}


      ### Testing and Validation Checklist


      Before declaring {feature_name} configuration complete, validate these scenarios
      with production-scale data:


      {validation_checklist}


      Configuration that produces accurate financial statements with 1,000 transactions
      often fails at 100,000+ transactions due to database query timeouts during financial
      close, report generation failures on multi-entity consolidations, or UI slowdowns
      when selecting from dropdown lists containing thousands of GL accounts or cost
      centers.

      '
