        Project Timesheet: Project timesheet configuration determines how time entries
          are captured, validated, approved, and billed to customers. Misconfigured
          timesheets create billing disputes, revenue leakage from unbilled hours,
          and project profitability reporting errors that mask actual project performance.
        Project Billing: Project billing configuration controls how time, expenses,
          and milestones translate into customer invoices. Incorrect billing rules
          create revenue recognition errors, undercharge customers by missing billable
          items, or damage client relationships through billing disputes requiring
          manual corrections.
        Expense Management: Expense management configuration defines submission workflows,
          approval hierarchies, expense categories, and reimbursement processing.
          Incorrect expense configuration creates compliance violations, duplicate
          reimbursements, policy enforcement failures, and financial reporting errors.
        Leave Management: Leave management configuration defines time-off policies,
          accrual rules, approval workflows, and calendar integration. Misconfigured
          leave systems create payroll errors, compliance violations with labor laws,
          scheduling conflicts, and employee dissatisfaction from policy inconsistencies.
        Performance Appraisal: Performance appraisal configuration defines review
          cycles, evaluation criteria, goal tracking, and feedback workflows. Poor
          appraisal configuration creates subjective bias in evaluations, incomplete
          performance documentation for employment decisions, goal misalignment across
          organization, and legal vulnerabilities in termination processes.
        Payroll Configuration: Payroll configuration establishes salary structures,
          tax calculation rules, benefit deductions, and payment processing automation.
          Misconfigured payroll creates tax compliance failures triggering penalties,
          incorrect net pay calculations damaging employee trust, benefit deduction
          errors, and financial reporting inaccuracies.
