          functionality. Proper configuration ensures seamless integration with your
          business processes and delivers expected outcomes. Misconfiguration creates
          operational friction that compounds into permanent inefficiencies, forcing
          users to develop workarounds that persist even after the underlying issue
          is fixed. Configuration decisions made here affect all users and transactions
          across the system.
      business_process:
        Project Timesheet: time tracking, billable hour management, and project profitability
          analysis
        Project Billing: project invoicing, revenue recognition, and client billing
          automation
        Expense Management: business expense tracking, reimbursement processing, and
          expense policy enforcement
        Leave Management: time-off request handling, absence tracking, and leave policy
          administration
        Performance Appraisal: employee evaluation, goal management, and performance
          review cycles
        Payroll Configuration: salary processing, tax withholding, and payroll compliance
        default: this feature supports business workflows by automating routine tasks,
          enforcing approval hierarchies, and maintaining audit trails. Configure
          process flows to match your organization's operational procedures while
          maintaining compliance with internal controls.
      configuration_steps:
        Project Timesheet: Navigate to Project > Configuration > Settings. Enable
          timesheet tracking. Configure time entry validation rules. Set up billable/non-billable
          classifications. Define project task associations. Configure approval workflows.
