        default: Integration with core Odoo modules and may require third-party module
          installation for extended functionality. Verify module compatibility with
          your Odoo version before enabling integration features.
      common_pitfall:
        Project Timesheet: Failing to configure timesheet locking causes approved
          entries to be modified retroactively, breaking billing integrity and requiring
          invoice corrections. Enable automatic locking of approved periods.
        Project Billing: Mixing billing types on a single project (e.g., time and
          materials plus fixed price) creates revenue recognition confusion. Use separate
          project phases or sale orders for different billing methods.
        Expense Management: Not enforcing receipt attachment requirements allows policy
          violations and creates audit trail gaps. Make receipt upload mandatory for
          all expense categories.
        Leave Management: Configuring unlimited negative leave balances allows employees
          to accrue leave debt that becomes financial liability on termination. Set
          maximum negative balance limits.
        Performance Appraisal: Running performance reviews during year-end holidays
          causes rushed evaluations and low completion rates. Schedule review cycles
          for non-holiday periods.
        Payroll Configuration: Processing payroll without thorough testing creates
          mass employee payment errors affecting morale and requiring emergency corrections.
          Test with sample employees first.
        default: The most common configuration mistake is incomplete prerequisite
          setup. Verify all dependent modules are installed, company settings are
          configured, and user permissions are assigned before attempting configuration.
          Skipping prerequisites causes cryptic error messages that are difficult
          to diagnose.
      troubleshooting_tips:
        Project Timesheet: If timesheets do not generate invoices, verify task is
          linked to sale order line, timesheet is approved and not locked for billing,
          billing type is correctly configured, and user has invoicing permissions.
        Project Billing: If invoices show incorrect amounts, check billing rate source
          priority, timesheet rounding rules, prepaid service balance, expense billability
          flags, and revenue recognition method.
        Expense Management: If expenses do not post to accounting, verify expense
          category maps to chart of accounts, expense is approved, accounting integration
          is enabled, and journal entry dates are valid.
        Leave Management: If leave balances are incorrect, check accrual rule start
          date matches hire date, leave type is correctly configured, carryover rules
