          Automatic loyalty liability accounting entries.
        default: Automated actions execute based on record triggers, field value changes,
          or scheduled timing. Configure automation carefully to prevent infinite
          loops, ensure idempotent operations, and handle error conditions gracefully.
      performance_considerations:
        Point Of Sale Offline Mode: Limit offline transaction cache to 1000 orders
          to prevent browser performance degradation. Configure incremental sync instead
          of full sync for large product catalogs. Enable data compression for offline
          storage. Monitor IndexedDB size and implement cleanup policies. Optimize
          product image caching for offline availability. Test offline mode performance
          with realistic transaction volumes before deployment.
        Point Of Sale Hardware Setup: Use wired connections instead of Bluetooth when
          possible for reliability. Configure print job batching for high-volume periods.
          Enable direct printing instead of browser print dialog. Use dedicated POS
          terminals instead of general-purpose computers. Configure device timeouts
          appropriate for hardware response times. Implement hardware pooling for
          multiple POS stations sharing printers.
        Point Of Sale Receipt Customization: Minimize receipt template complexity
          to reduce rendering time. Optimize logo file size (recommended under 50KB).
          Use standard fonts instead of custom fonts when possible. Limit dynamic
          content requiring database lookups. Configure receipt preview caching for
          repeat transactions. Test receipt printing speed during peak transaction
          periods.
        Point Of Sale Loyalty: Index customer lookup fields (phone, email, card number)
          for fast searches. Cache active loyalty programs in POS session. Configure
          point calculation server-side to prevent client manipulation. Limit loyalty
          history display to recent 90 days to improve load times. Implement point
          balance caching with periodic refresh. Monitor loyalty calculation impact
          on checkout speed during peak hours.
        default: Monitor performance impact on system resources. Large-scale deployments
          may require infrastructure scaling, database optimization, or workflow adjustments
          to maintain acceptable response times.
      common_pitfall:
        Point Of Sale Offline Mode: Operating offline for extended periods (days)
          creates massive sync backlogs causing data conflicts and timeout failures.
          Set maximum offline duration of 8 hours before requiring reconnection and
          sync.
        Point Of Sale Hardware Setup: Not testing hardware failover scenarios causes
          checkout disruptions when printer jams or payment terminal fails. Configure
          backup devices and train staff on manual fallback procedures.
        Point Of Sale Receipt Customization: Adding too much information to receipts
          creates long receipts wasting paper and annoying customers. Keep receipts
          concise showing only essential transaction details and legal requirements.
        Point Of Sale Loyalty: Changing point earning ratios retroactively creates
          customer dissatisfaction and loyalty program distrust. Grandfather existing
          members under old rules when changing program terms.
        default: The most common configuration mistake is incomplete prerequisite
          setup. Verify all dependent modules are installed, company settings are
          configured, and user permissions are assigned before attempting configuration.
          Skipping prerequisites causes cryptic error messages that are difficult
          to diagnose.
      troubleshooting_tips:
        Point Of Sale Offline Mode: If synchronization fails repeatedly, check browser
          IndexedDB limits not exceeded, verify server API endpoints responding, confirm
          user permissions for data sync, and review conflict resolution logs for
          transaction duplicates.
        Point Of Sale Hardware Setup: If devices not detected, verify USB cables connected
          properly, check device drivers installed and updated, confirm IoT Box network
          connectivity, test device independently outside Odoo, and review browser
          hardware access permissions.
        Point Of Sale Receipt Customization: If receipts print incorrectly, verify
          printer paper width matches template configuration, check logo dimensions
          within printer memory limits, confirm font encoding supports special characters,
          test receipt preview before printing, and validate printer firmware version
          compatibility.
        Point Of Sale Loyalty: If points not calculating correctly, verify loyalty
          program active dates include current date, check customer assigned to correct
          loyalty program, confirm product eligible for point earning, review point
          calculation formula configuration, and test with manual point calculation
          to isolate issue.
        default: 'If configuration does not behave as expected: (1) Check server logs
          for error messages, (2) Verify user has required permissions, (3) Confirm
          prerequisite modules are installed, (4) Test in developer mode to see detailed
          error information, (5) Review recent configuration changes that might have
          introduced the issue.'
      validation_checklist:
        Point Of Sale Offline Mode: Simulate network failure during active POS session,
          verify transactions save locally, restore network and confirm automatic
          synchronization, test conflict resolution with duplicate orders, validate
          inventory accuracy post-sync, and verify no data loss during offline period
        Point Of Sale Hardware Setup: Test receipt printing with various transaction
          types, scan barcodes to verify product lookup, verify cash drawer opens
          on sale completion, process test card payment through terminal, confirm
          customer display shows correct information, and test all devices simultaneously
          under load
        Point Of Sale Receipt Customization: Print test receipts on actual thermal
          printer, verify logo displays correctly at correct size, confirm all legal
          information present and legible, test receipt with long product names, validate
          tax breakdown accuracy, check promotional messages display correctly, and
          verify receipt barcode scans properly for returns
        Point Of Sale Loyalty: Complete transaction with loyalty customer, verify
          points calculated correctly, test point redemption at checkout, confirm
          tier upgrade triggers properly, validate point expiration logic, test loyalty
          card barcode scanning, verify email notifications sent correctly, and confirm
          accounting entries for loyalty liability
        default: 'Before deploying configuration to production: (1) Test with sample
          data in development environment, (2) Verify user permissions grant appropriate
          access, (3) Confirm integration with related modules works correctly, (4)
          Document configuration decisions and expected behavior, (5) Create database
          backup, (6) Train users on new functionality, (7) Monitor system behavior
          for first week after deployment.'
