          '
        default: Available functionality includes country-specific functionality including
          tax calculations, legal compliance, and local accounting standards. Configuration
          adapts Odoo's global capabilities to meet regional regulatory requirements.
      tax_system_configuration:
        Localization Usa: 'The US tax system in Odoo requires configuring both federal
          and state-level sales tax based on your nexus jurisdictions. Navigate to
          Accounting > Configuration > Taxes to create tax records for each state
          where you have physical presence or economic nexus (typically USD 100,000
          in sales or 200 transactions). Enable origin-based or destination-based
          sourcing rules depending on state requirements - most states use destination-based
          except for origin-based states like Arizona, Illinois, Mississippi, and
          others. Configure tax mapping by product category (taxable goods, exempt
          food items, digital services) and enable automatic tax calculation using
          TaxJar or Avalara integration for real-time rate updates based on 10,000+
          jurisdiction changes annually.

          '
        Localization Uk: 'UK VAT configuration requires setting up three primary tax
          rates - 20% standard rate for most goods/services, 5% reduced rate for domestic
          fuel and children''s car seats, and 0% zero rate for books, food, and children''s
          clothing. Access Accounting > Configuration > Taxes and configure each tax
          with the appropriate account mappings for VAT collected (liability account)
          and VAT paid (asset account). Enable Making Tax Digital (MTD) connectivity
          through Settings > Accounting > Fiscal Localization > UK MTD Settings, entering
          your Government Gateway credentials and authorizing Odoo to submit VAT returns
          on your behalf. Configure VAT schemes if using Flat Rate (for businesses
          under £150k turnover) or Cash Accounting (for businesses under £1.35m turnover)
          by adjusting tax realization from invoice date to payment date.

          '
        Localization Germany: 'German VAT (Umsatzsteuer) requires configuring 19%
          standard rate and 7% reduced rate for food, books, and cultural services
          through Accounting > Configuration > Taxes. Enable reverse charge mechanism
